Create Date Table, Measures and Calculated Column 8

Step 1 - Create Date Table

 

.Calendar = ADDCOLUMNS(
            CALENDAR(MIN('fatal-police-shootings-data'[date]),
                       MAX('fatal-police-shootings-data'[date])
                    ),
            "Year", FORMAT ([Date], "YYYY"),
            "Quarter", FORMAT ([Date], "q"),
            "Month", FORMAT ([Date], "mmm"))

                 

  1.  Copy the above Dax formula to create a Date table
  2.  Then connect the Date table and the Fatal-Police-Shootings-Data table using the Date Column

Follow the Gif below to create a Date Table



Step 2 - Create Measures


1.  Copy each  Dax formula listed below to create the different measures

.Total Fleers Killed =
        CALCULATE(COUNT('fatal-police-shootings-data'[flee]),
        FILTER ('fatal-police-shootings-data',
        'fatal-police-shootings-data'[flee]="car" ||
        'fatal-police-shootings-data'[flee]="foot"||
        'fatal-police-shootings-data'[flee]="other"))
 
%Fleers killed=
         DIVIDE ([Total Fleers Killed], [.Total Fatalities])
 
.Total Fatalities =
             CALCULATE(
             COUNTA('fatal-police-shootings-data'[id]),
             ALL('fatal-police-shootings-data'[flee]))
 
.LY Fleers Killed = CALCULATE(
            [Total Fleers Killed],
            DATEADD('.Calendar'[Date],-1,YEAR))
 
.YOY Diff = ([Total Fleers Killed] - [.LY Fleers Killed])
 
.YOY rev Arrow = var Up = UNICHAR(9650)
             var Down = UNICHAR(9660) return if([.YOY Diff]> 1 ,Up, Down)
 
.YOY rev Arrow Condition = if([.YOY Diff] > 1 , 1, 0)
 
 YoY =
      IF(ISBLANK(VAR __PREV_YEAR = CALCULATE([.Total Fleers Killed],
        DATEADD('.Calendar'[Date].[Date], -1, YEAR))
      RETURN
        DIVIDE([.Total Fleers Killed] - __PREV_YEAR, __PREV_YEAR)),0,VAR __PREV_YEAR = CALCULATE([.Total          Fleers Killed],    DATEADD('.Calendar'[Date].[Date], -1, YEAR))
      RETURN
        DIVIDE([.Total Fleers Killed] - __PREV_YEAR, __PREV_YEAR))
